title.narrative: 001 HEALTH SYSTEM STRENGTHENING (HSS)

description.narrative: 'By 2025, National and sub-national health system capacity strengthened for increased coverage of high impact equitable resilient MNCAH interventions including in emergency settings, which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 'By 2025, newborns, children, adolescent girls and women benefit from an equitable, high-quality and resilient health system across the continuum of care

description.narrative: UNICEF provided strategic directions and inputs in the development and launching of national strategies and multi-years plans including: the National Newborn and Child Survival Strategy (2021-2025), Health Extension Optimization Road Map 2021-2022, National Equity in Health Service Strategic Plan 2021-2022 Health Information Strategic Plan and Road Map 2021-2025 and National Medical;Oxygen;and Pulse Oximetry Scale Up;Road Map;(2016-2021/21). Birth notification rate is incorporated as a national health indicator disaggregated by facility and community. Birth notification at facility level has reached 67% from 54.4% in 2020 and number of children notified from facilities and live births are captured in the DHIS-2 platform. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
